  27 /* Unicode 3.0.1 does not contain all the characters in GBK.  Define
  28    USE_PRIVATE_AREA to 1 in order to use mappings from/to the Unicode
  29    Private Use area.  Until we see other systems using the same mappings,
  30    it is disabled.  */
  31 #define USE_PRIVATE_AREA 0
  32 
  33 /* The conversion table to UCS4 has almost no holes.  It can be generated with:
  34 
  35    perl tab.pl < gbk.txt
  36 
  37    where tab.pl is:
  38    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  39    $n=0;
  40    while (<>) {
  41      local($gbk, $ucs4, %rest) = split;
  42      local($u)=hex($ucs4);
  43      local($g)=hex($gbk);
  44      printf ("\n ") if ($n % 4 eq 0);
  45      ++$n;
  46      printf (" [0x%04x] = 0x%04x,",
  47              int(($g - 0x8140) / 256) * 192 + (($g - 0x8140) & 0xff), $u);
  48    }
  49    printf ("\n");
  50 
  51    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
  52  */

13123 /* Definitions used in the body of the `gconv' function.  */
13124 #define CHARSET_NAME        "GBK//"
13125 #define FROM_LOOP       from_gbk
13126 #define TO_LOOP         to_gbk
13127 #define DEFINE_INIT     1
13128 #define DEFINE_FINI     1
13129 #define MIN_NEEDED_FROM     1
13130 #define MAX_NEEDED_FROM     2
13131 #define MIN_NEEDED_TO       4
13132 #define ONE_DIRECTION       0
13133 
13134 
13135 /* First define the conversion function from GBK to UCS4.  */
13136 #define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT    MIN_NEEDED_FROM
13137 #define MAX_NEEDED_INPUT    MAX_NEEDED_FROM
13138 #define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT   MIN_NEEDED_TO
13139 #define LOOPFCT         FROM_LOOP
13140 #define BODY \
13141   {                                       \
13142     uint32_t ch = *inptr;                             \
13143                                           \
13144     if (ch <= 0x7f)                               \
13145       ++inptr;                                    \
13146     else                                      \
13147       if (__builtin_expect (ch <= 0x80, 0)                    \
13148       || __builtin_expect (ch > 0xfe, 0))                     \
13149     {                                     \
13150       if (__glibc_likely (ch == 0x80))                    \
13151         {                                     \
13152           /* Exception for the Euro sign (see CP936).  */             \
13153           ch = 0x20ac;                            \
13154           ++inptr;                                \
13155         }                                     \
13156       else                                    \
13157         {                                     \
13158           /* This is illegal.  */                         \
13159           STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1);                 \
13160         }                                     \
13161     }                                     \
13162       else                                    \
13163     {                                     \
13164       /* Two or more byte character.  First test whether the          \
13165          next byte is also available.  */                     \
13166       uint32_t ch2;                               \
13167       int idx;                                \
13168                                           \
13169       if (__glibc_unlikely (inptr + 1 >= inend))                  \
13170         {                                     \
13171           /* The second character is not available.  Store            \
13172          the intermediate result.  */                     \
13173           result = __GCONV_INCOMPLETE_INPUT;                  \
13174           break;                                  \
13175         }                                     \
13176                                           \
13177       ch2 = inptr[1];                             \
13178                                           \
13179       /* All second bytes of a multibyte character must be >= 0x40, and   \
13180          the __gbk_to_ucs table only covers the range up to 0xfe 0xa0. */ \
13181       if (__builtin_expect (ch2 < 0x40, 0)                    \
13182           || (__builtin_expect (ch, 0x81) == 0xfe && ch2 > 0xa0))         \
13183         {                                     \
13184           /* This is an illegal character.  */                \
13185           STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (1);                 \
13186         }                                     \
13187                                           \
13188       /* This is code set 1: GBK.  */                     \
13189       idx = (ch - 0x81)*192 + (ch2 - 0x40);                   \
13190                                           \
13191       ch = __gbk_to_ucs[idx];                         \
13192                                           \
13193       if (__builtin_expect (ch, 1) == 0 && *inptr != '\0')            \
13194         {                                     \
13195           /* This is an illegal character.  */                \
13196           STANDARD_FROM_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (2);                 \
13197         }                                     \
13198                                           \
13199       inptr += 2;                                 \
13200     }                                     \
13201                                           \
13202     put32 (outptr, ch);                               \
13203     outptr += 4;                                  \
13204   }
13205 #define LOOP_NEED_FLAGS
13206 #define ONEBYTE_BODY \
13207   {                                       \
13208     if (c < 0x80)                                 \
13209       return c;                                   \
13210     else                                      \
13211       return WEOF;                                \
13212   }
13213 #include <iconv/loop.c>
13214

13216 /* Next, define the other direction.  */
13217 #define MIN_NEEDED_INPUT    MIN_NEEDED_TO
13218 #define MIN_NEEDED_OUTPUT   MIN_NEEDED_FROM
13219 #define MAX_NEEDED_OUTPUT   MAX_NEEDED_FROM
13220 #define LOOPFCT         TO_LOOP
13221 #define BODY \
13222   {                                       \
13223     uint32_t ch = get32 (inptr);                          \
13224     char buf[2];                                  \
13225     const char *cp = buf;                             \
13226                                           \
13227     if (ch <= L'\x7f')                                \

13229       *outptr++ = (unsigned char) ch;                         \

13423       break;                                  \
13424     case 0x33d1:                                  \
13425       cp = "\xa9\x52";                            \
13426       break;                                  \
13427     case 0x33d2:                                  \
13428       cp = "\xa9\x53";                            \
13429       break;                                  \
13430     case 0x33d5:                                  \
13431       cp = "\xa9\x54";                            \
13432       break;                                  \
13433     case 0x4e00 ... 0x9fa5:                           \
13434       cp = __gbk_from_ucs4_tab8[ch - 0x4e00];                 \
13435       break;                                  \
13436     case 0xe7c7 ... 0xe864:                           \
13437       cp = USE_PRIVATE_AREA ? __gbk_from_ucs4_tab9[ch - 0xe7c7] : "\0\0"; \
13438       break;                                  \
13439     case 0xf92c:                                  \
13440       cp = "\xfd\x9c";                            \
13441       break;                                  \
13442     case 0xf979:                                  \
13443       cp = "\xfd\x9d";                            \
13444       break;                                  \
13445     case 0xf995:                                  \
13446       cp = "\xfd\x9e";                            \
13447       break;                                  \
13448     case 0xf9e7:                                  \
13449       cp = "\xfd\x9f";                            \
13450       break;                                  \
13451     case 0xf9f1:                                  \
13452       cp = "\xfd\xa0";                            \
13453       break;                                  \
13454     case 0xfa0c ... 0xfa29:                           \
13455       cp = __gbk_from_ucs4_tab10[ch - 0xfa0c];                \
13456       break;                                  \
13457     case 0xfe30 ... 0xfe6b:                           \
13458       cp = __gbk_from_ucs4_tab11[ch - 0xfe30];                \
13459       break;                                  \
13460     case 0xff01 ... 0xff5e:                           \
13461       cp = __gbk_from_ucs4_tab12[ch - 0xff01];                \
13462       break;                                  \
13463     case 0xffe0 ... 0xffe5:                           \
13464       cp = "\xa1\xe9\0\0\xa1\xea\0\0\xa9\x56\0\0\xa3\xfe\0\0\xa9\x57\0\0\xa3\xa4" + ((ch - 0xffe0) * 4); \
13465       break;                                  \
13466     default:                                  \
13467       UNICODE_TAG_HANDLER (ch, 4);                        \
13468       cp = "";                                \
13469       break;                                  \
13470     }                                     \
13471       if (__builtin_expect (cp[0], '\1') == '\0' && ch != 0)              \
13472     {                                     \
13473       /* Illegal character.  */                       \
13474       STANDARD_TO_LOOP_ERR_HANDLER (4);                   \
13475     }                                     \
13476       /* See whether there is enough room for the second byte we write.  */   \
13477       else if (cp[1] != '\0' && __builtin_expect (outptr + 1 >= outend, 0))   \
13478     {                                     \
13479       /* We have not enough room.  */                     \
13480       result = __GCONV_FULL_OUTPUT;                       \
13481       break;                                  \
13482     }                                     \
13483       else                                    \
13484     {                                     \
13485       *outptr++ = cp[0];                              \
13486       if (cp[1] != '\0')                              \
13487         *outptr++ = cp[1];                            \
13488     }                                     \
13489     }                                         \
13490                                           \
13491     inptr += 4;                                                               \
13492   }
